The course gives and overview of the different aspects of the work in the communication professional field (e.g. organizational communication, internal communication, mapping stakeholders, planning communication, diferent types of communicational texts, media relations etc).Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to give background knowledge needed for beginning their career in the field of communication. The course is followed by the second partwhere the students  implement the acquired knowledge by solving different practical tasks.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  When a student has completed the course successfully, he/she can: - explain the tasks of communication managers in different organizations; - choose between different communication activities based on the objectives and stakeholders of an organization; - plan and analyse everyday communication activities.
